<subSubSection type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageNumber="53">
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:239684" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Solenopsis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-HNS="Solenopsis scelesta" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="scelesta">Solenopsis scelesta</taxonomicName>
is a relatively gracile species that can be recognized by the following combination of character states: head width&gt; 0.4 mm; compound eyes comprised of about 8-10 ommatidia; dorsal propodeal face about twice as long as declivitous face; dorsal face of propodeum smooth and without sculpture. Material from Paraguay is a close match to Forel’s types from 
<normalizedToken originalValue="São">Sao</normalizedToken>
Paulo. I have not examined Emery’s type of 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:36259" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Solenopsis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-HNS="Solenopsis decipiens Emery" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="decipiens">S. decipiens</taxonomicName>
, but Forel’s description of 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:152136" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Solenopsis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-HNS="Solenopsis decipiens scelesta Forel" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="variety" species="decipiens" variety="scelesta">S. scelesta</taxonomicName>
based on differences in thoracic structure, antennal scape length, and eye size suggests that it is unlikely that both forms are conspecific. I change the status of 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:239684" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Solenopsis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-HNS="Solenopsis scelesta" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="scelesta">Solenopsis scelesta</taxonomicName>
to eliminate the trinomen.
</paragraph>
